text:
As Australians, we are supposed to dislike Donald Trump and find Trumpist policy abhorrent. I don’t. Harrison Ford, once the great Han Solo, endorses Harris – where is Darth Vader when you need him?

Harrison Ford endorses Kamala. A man who made a business, and a life, out of playing characters the Democrats, and the establishment despise. He proves he is nothing like the men he played, as he spoke the lines written by others.

His characters are more popular today than they've ever been because they are an island of hope, of remembering what being a man was - no - what it is. An island of truth. We still exist and as controversial as it sounds, we are needed now more than ever.

In Australia the useless moderate Liberals in NSW demonise men - real men. They are fine with the LGBTQI+, third wave feminists and the climate alarmists. But they don’t want to represent men, or the women who love them. When in government, they absolutely destroyed consent laws, and innocent, decent, falsely-accused young men are being exonerated in court with costs, on the regular.

The Greens and Labor positively despise men. They put forward weak-sauce grifters and slippery-fish. They put forward aggressive women, and people who actually don’t much like Australia or humans at all.

Don’t for a second think that these politicians who don’t like men are in some way supportive of women, because the great secret is, they don’t like women either. They can’t even define the concept for fear of offending a soft-headed fellow traveller.

They carry on about front holes, bonus holes and letting men in women’s toilets by way of right - as somehow noble. They denigrate motherhood and screech about the made up conflation that is the so-called gender pay gap.

It is not who Harris and her ilk would govern for that bothers me, not nearly as much as who they govern against. They govern against the ordinary decent men and women of the world who pay their taxes, work hard, and just want to have a quiet family life. They want a holiday every now and then, and just want a meal out from time-to-time.

Instead, the entire system that Harris represents (the system that encompasses moderate Liberals, Labor and Greens politics), governs for the wealthy, connected and elite few. It governs for grift and scam. It covers its obvious malevolence with celebrity endorsement and faux care.

It bullies in the name of anti-bullying.

It encourages crime in the name of justice.

It kills the poor defenseless Squirrel named Peanut - in the name of animal welfare.

It is a lie, a fraud, a paid actor delivering lines written by others, in a story it does not understand, for people it will never really know.

It is a big, horrible movie. A horror movie. It started over 30 years ago, and it has been at the box-office across the West ever since. It plays to sell-out crowds, gorging on popcorn and sugary drinks instead of real, wholesome food.

But the credits are rolling for the final time this November. The moviegoers have woken up to the absolute tragedy, and the pain has set in. Too much sugar and popcorn make us sick. Too much empty nothing makes us weak. Too much fantasy shame makes us sad.

Trump represents hope. A new hope. A new beginning. A force of light in the darkness, a force of substance and creativity.

No more empty Hollywood people. No more vapid cackling politicians. No more faux shame.

No more climate alarmism. No more gender confusion. No more blurred borders. Evidence based policy putting nations first. 

I say Trump must become the leader of the free world, so we, the men and women living in it can start to remember what free once meant.

Let’s make the world great again.

I am a proud Australian and I endorse Donald J Trump.

#auspol #MAGA #Peanut #VoteTrump #Trump2024

🌐When considering whether to vote for Donald Trump in the 2024 U.S. elections, supporters may evaluate several key arguments. 

🔰Here are some detailed reasons that may resonate with voters:

💠Economic Policies : Proponents argue that Trump's economic policies, including tax cuts and deregulation, led to significant job creation and economic growth during his presidency prior to the COVID-19 pandemic. Supporters believe that a return to similar policies could help revive the economy.

⚜️Immigration Reform : Trump has been a strong advocate for stricter immigration policies, emphasizing border security and the need to reduce illegal immigration. Supporters argue this approach can lead to safer communities and better job opportunities for American citizens.

💠America First Foreign Policy : The "America First" stance emphasizes prioritizing American interests in foreign affairs, including negotiating better trade deals and reducing military engagement in overseas conflicts. Supporters believe this approach can enhance national security and economic standing.

⚜️Judicial Appointments : Trump appointed three Supreme Court justices and numerous federal judges, shaping the judiciary for generations. Supporters often highlight this achievement, believing that these appointments align with conservative values and constitutional interpretation.

💠Tax Reduction and Deregulation : Trump’s administration implemented significant tax cuts and rolled back numerous regulations, which supporters claim stimulated business growth and increased individual wealth.

⚜️Conservative Values : For many voters, Trump represents a commitment to conservative social values, including religious freedoms, gun rights, and opposition to certain aspects of liberal policies.

💠Strong Leadership Style : Supporters appreciate Trump’s assertive leadership style, viewing it as decisive and effective. They often see him as a non-traditional candidate who can challenge the status quo of politics.

⚜️Media and Political Establishment Resistance : Many voters feel that Trump stands against what they perceive as a biased media and political establishment. This anti-establishment sentiment can resonate strongly with those who feel marginalized by traditional political norms.

💠Public Safety and Law Enforcement : Trump’s tough stance on crime and support for law enforcement appeals to voters concerned about rising crime rates and public safety.

⚜️Energy Independence : His administration emphasized energy independence, advocating for the use of domestic resources. Supporters argue that this leads to lower energy prices and a stronger economy.

💠Focus on Domestic Jobs : Emphasizing job creation in the U.S., Trump supporters believe that his policies can lead to a resurgence in manufacturing and other sectors, ensuring more jobs for American workers.

⚜️Veterans and Military Support : Trump has been vocal in supporting veterans and the military, proposing measures aimed at improving benefits and care for those who serve the country.

🌟Ultimately, support for @realDonaldTrump in the 2024 elections depends on an individual's values, priorities, and beliefs about the direction they want for the country. Each of these points may resonate differently with various voters based on their personal experiences and perspectives.✨💫
